OL,6,FA farm built by poet Robert Burns
OL,7,Fwhich is in a "serious state of
OL,8,Fdeterioration" has been given a
OL,9,Flifeline after receiving nearly
OL,10,F#500,000 of funding.
OL,12,FA celebrated Dumfries and Galloway
OL,13,Ffarm where poet Robert Burns penned
OL,14,Fsome of his famous work, including
OL,15,FAuld Lang Syne, has stepped closer to
OL,16,Fits future being secured.
OL,18,FNearly #500,000 of National Lottery
OL,19,FHeritage funding, which could rise up
OL,20,Fto #1.6m, is set to contribute to
OL,21,Fsafeguarding the site's future.
